A NON-GOVERNMENTAL Organisation, Muungano wa Jamii Tanzania (MUJATA), has introduced special village conflict management councils in all wards in the Tarime and Rorya districts, to empower the communities to identify major causes of lawlessness at grassroots level. The organisation is geared towards speedy implementation of a three-year project starting this year aimed at creating a law abiding society by encouraging wananchi to volunteer information about criminals before they strike. It is embarking on identifying policies that strain the police-community relationship and make it harder for police to gain trust and, ultimately.